      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LITTLE COINTREAU (3) is close to breaking through, last start finishing just a head away in second over 1700m at Alpha. Has the early speed to cross from out wide. Winning hoop Satherley reunites and has the class to find the winners' list. HEAVENLY LEGEND (2) showed good early muster and fought on to finish second last start over 1000m at Barcaldine. Well placed and there is no reason why he cannot salute. SCHMOOZER (4) started at $10 last time on the back of a win at Longreach two starts ago but was below his best, finishing tenth over 1700m at Alpha. Robert Faehr gets the best out of this seven-year-old gelding. Tackling a more suitable race this time so he will be hard to beat. INQUISITIVE LEGEND (6) was a placegetter on dirt over 1100m at Longreach two back but missed the frame on turf over 1000m at Barcaldine last time. Well worth another chance returning to the dirt this time.",
